<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

